    "created_at": "2011-10-24T18:33:58Z",
    "updated_at": "2011-10-24T18:33:58Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "That might be a bit harder than it sounds.  The pylab_activate function does print the message (exactly as it should, for example when invoked by the %pylab magic).  The problem is, the Widget doesn't know what the pylab backend will be until the kernel has started, and printed the message, by which time the widget banner has long-since been drawn, so changing it will have no effect.\n\nOf course, an easier option would be to allow you to disable printing the 'welcome to pylab' message outright, so that you could prevent it from appearing, just like you can do with the banner.\n"
  },
