    "created_at": "2011-11-22T20:24:05Z",
    "updated_at": "2011-11-22T20:24:05Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Yes, unfortunately it simply can't be added to the banner, because `pylab_activate` can be called at _any time_, way after the kernel is already running and the banner is long gone.  In that regard, I think we should simply close this issue, because there is simply no way to do what the title requests.  At most, we can add a 'quiet' flag to `pylab_activate`, so that users who are customizing things can call it themselves with `quiet=True` so it doesn't print anything and instead.  @punchagan, would that work for you?\n"
  },
