    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "This might be a good solution for everyone: have `pylab_activate` unconditionally _return_ the string it would print, and have it print it if `quiet==False`.  That way, customizers can capture it and use it in their own way, while interactive use remains unmodified.  How does that sound?\n"
