    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "@fperez - that would work, but it puts the config on the kernel side, rather than the frontend.  Print messages that result from startup are clearly distinguishable (no parent) at the frontend.  The advantage here is that it is most likely for frontend embedders to want to flip this switch, and it's slightly harder to propagate config to the kernel than it is to set a flag in the frontend.\n"
